813
01:06:44,740 --> 01:06:58,605
[SPEAKER_00]: All of the funds that were raised from private citizens in Medford or major corporations in and around the Medford area is all that was inside of our building today.

814
01:06:59,706 --> 01:07:05,448
[SPEAKER_00]: That is for all of our patrons and for the citizens in the city of Medford.

815
01:07:08,149 --> 01:07:14,671
[SPEAKER_00]: I will tell you that there were donors that were in the $300,000 mark or even maybe more.

816
01:07:15,111 --> 01:07:19,493
[SPEAKER_00]: But there were also donors that were a $5 donor or a $10 donor.

817
01:07:20,393 --> 01:07:28,996
[SPEAKER_00]: The library is meant for every single patron and our citizens in the city of Medford, as well as we welcome other communities.

818
01:07:30,116 --> 01:07:41,880
[SPEAKER_00]: And the budget that is in front of you tonight is just a very basic budget to keep the building workable and servicing the patrons.

819
01:07:42,580 --> 01:07:45,661
[SPEAKER_00]: It's not an elaborate budget by any means.

820
01:07:46,462 --> 01:07:55,005
[SPEAKER_00]: And hopefully in years to come, we would like to see that we could improve and increase the budget and offer much more than we're offering right now today.

821
01:07:55,905 --> 01:08:01,188
[SPEAKER_00]: with again, you know, other services, including more personnel.

822
01:08:01,909 --> 01:08:06,992
[SPEAKER_00]: I was on a Sunday, you know, there were many things that we would like to improve upon.

823
01:08:07,652 --> 01:08:12,855
[SPEAKER_00]: But before I end this evening, I'd like to tell you just a quick story.

824
01:08:14,398 --> 01:08:19,900
